underlying_goal: Commit a set of unrelated local changes into separate, logical git commits.
primary_success: Successfully identified four distinct sets of changes and, after getting user confirmation, created four separate, atomic commits with clear messages.
brief_summary: After pulling remote changes, the user asked to commit local work. Claude identified four unrelated sets of changes, proposed creating separate commits for each, and executed this plan after user approval, resulting in a clean git history with four atomic commits.
